  <data key="d0">Antonino Tumeo</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Antonino Tumeo is an author associated with PNNL at Richland, WA, USA on the MLIR-based Compiler Flow project.&lt;SEP&gt;Antonino Tumeo is an author of the paper on MLIR-based compiler flow for system-level design and hardware acceleration.&lt;SEP&gt;Antonino Tumeo is a co-author of the ML-CGRA paper and has email antonino.tumeo@pnnl.gov.&lt;SEP&gt;Antonino Tumeo is a researcher from Pacific Northwest National Laboratory involved in the development of VecPAC.&lt;SEP&gt;Antonino Tumeo is an author of multiple research papers on reconfigurable architectures.&lt;SEP&gt;Antonino Tumeo is a researcher associated with the development of DRIPS.&lt;SEP&gt;Antonino Tumeo is a researcher who has worked with Ang Li and Kevin Barker on several projects.</data>
