<node id="Loop Tiling">
  <data key="d0">Loop Tiling</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Loop tiling is a technique to optimize code by partitioning loops into smaller tiles for better parallelism.&lt;SEP&gt;Loop Tiling is a pass that tiles input/output tensors based on buffer size to maximize the usage of on-chip memory/registers in CGRAs.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-26064d6a9f50906d6ea350494b2c8125&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-16f1a6bd6447df0c77352ebdfefe35e0</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1766322487</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="MLIR Dialects">
  <data key="d0">MLIR Dialects</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">MLIR dialects are domain-specific languages used in SODA-OPT for outlining and tiling operations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-26064d6a9f50906d6ea350494b2c8125</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1766313379</data>
