  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">FPGA stands for Field-Programmable Gate Array, a type of hardware target for SODA-OPT's accelerators.&lt;SEP&gt;FPGA stands for Field-Programmable Gate Array and refers to a type of hardware accelerator.&lt;SEP&gt;Field-programmable gate array (FPGA) is a type of hardware that can be reconfigured to implement different applications but does not provide the same level of specialization as an ASIC, making it less efficient in certain contexts compared to CGRAs.&lt;SEP&gt;FPGA stands for Field-Programmable Gate Array, a type of integrated circuit whose logic blocks can be configured after manufacturing.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-28dc18967653f15f5790c6607c1d02e1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-434fe16e9313a890ebca0145e7c4f4e7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d3b54ca06794c60a35a49b96c496c299&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-72c65d5d8186bf9226fd5144f638e4f4</data>
