<node id="CGRA-Opt">
  <data key="d0">CGRA-Opt</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">CGRA-Opt is a framework for optimizing computations using CGRAs with specific passes for optimization.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-16f1a6bd6447df0c77352ebdfefe35e0</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1766322487</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Operation Fusion">
  <data key="d0">Operation Fusion</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Operation Fusion is an optimization technique used to merge element-wise operations on tensors, reducing data movement and improving resource utilization in CGRAs.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-16f1a6bd6447df0c77352ebdfefe35e0</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1766322487</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Pattern Matching">
  <data key="d0">Pattern Matching</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Pattern Matching is an optimization technique that recognizes patterns in tensor-based ML operations for direct acceleration by pre-configured CGRA templates.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-16f1a6bd6447df0c77352ebdfefe35e0</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1766322487</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="CGRA-Runner">
  <data key="d0">CGRA-Runner</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">CGRA-Runner is a runtime library and interface introduced to facilitate cycle-level and RTL simulation of CGRAs, aiding in the development and evaluation of the framework.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-16f1a6bd6447df0c77352ebdfefe35e0</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1766322487</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="CGRA Function Call">
  <data key="d0">CGRA Function Call</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">CGRA Function Call represents an accelerator command used by the CGRA runner to evaluate execution performance post-operation lowering.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-16f1a6bd6447df0c77352ebdfefe35e0</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1766322487</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Element-Wise Operations Fusion">
  <data key="d0">Element-Wise Operations Fusion</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Element-Wise Operations Fusion is a specific example of operation fusion where three operations (addf, maxf, and addf) are fused for data flow acceleration on CGRA tiles.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-16f1a6bd6447df0c77352ebdfefe35e0</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1766322487</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Double-Buffering Technique">
  <data key="d0">Double-Buffering Technique</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Double-Buffering Technique is a technique applied on ML-CGRA to minimize data communication delay by using two buffers.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-16f1a6bd6447df0c77352ebdfefe35e0</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1766322487</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
