<node id="PyMTL3">
  <data key="d0">PyMTL3</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">PyMTL3 is a Python-based modeling and simulation tool for hardware design.&lt;SEP&gt;PyMTL3 is used to model VecPAC and other CGRA configurations, generating synthesizable Verilog code.&lt;SEP&gt;PyMTL3 is used to model the DRIPS CGRA and related components at various levels of detail.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-867038b972ebe25908221a61e9ba9a9c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-68c4558c96bf4490d4f7c6a8af629f49&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-204207b9dedb6d8465abf466a8da7b22</data>
