<node id="TRANSPIRE [22]">
  <data key="d0">TRANSPIRE [22]</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">TRANSPIRE is a precision-aware CGRA that uses transprecision floating-point units to operate on multiple number formats.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-fb7fb6bd238c27a13ccbffd80022a059</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1766322523</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="PX-CGRA [4]">
  <data key="d0">PX-CGRA [4]</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">PX-CGRA employs polymorphic-approximated ALU clusters for modeling an accuracy-configurable CGRA, but it integrates additional arithmetic units which increase its area.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-fb7fb6bd238c27a13ccbffd80022a059</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1766322523</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="ASAP [25]">
  <data key="d0">ASAP [25]</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">ASAP is a hardware/software co-design framework that automatically synthesizes area-efficient and precision-aware CGRAs for specific applications without supporting vector computations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-fb7fb6bd238c27a13ccbffd80022a059</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1766322523</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="BioCare [9]">
  <data key="d0">BioCare [9]</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">BioCare integrates ALUs with two different execution modes to trade-off accuracy for energy efficiency but is specialized in a single application domain.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-fb7fb6bd238c27a13ccbffd80022a059</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1766322523</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="BitFusion [23]">
  <data key="d0">BitFusion [23]</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">BitFusion is a bit-level dynamically composable spatial accelerator for Deep Neural Networks (DNNs).</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-fb7fb6bd238c27a13ccbffd80022a059</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1766322523</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="VecPAC's Fused Functional Units">
  <data key="d0">VecPAC's Fused Functional Units</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">VecPAC is a hybrid CGRA design that can fuse functional units for maximizing performance and efficiency across different application domains.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-fb7fb6bd238c27a13ccbffd80022a059</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1766322524</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Coarse-Grained Reconfigurable Arrays">
  <data key="d0">Coarse-Grained Reconfigurable Arrays</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">CGRAs are tiled architectures composed of functional units interconnected through an on-chip network, offering higher efficiency than fine-grained reconfigurable devices while maintaining adaptability to different computational patterns.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-709227a765c55f9d3440bf6ca2a72a60</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1766322524</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Google">
  <data key="d0">Google</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Google is a company involved in the development and support of VecPAC.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-709227a765c55f9d3440bf6ca2a72a60</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1766322524</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Arizona State University">
  <data key="d0">Arizona State University</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Arizona State University contributes to the development of VecPAC with its researchers and employees.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-709227a765c55f9d3440bf6ca2a72a60</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1766322524</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
