<node id="DRIPS">
  <data key="d0">DRIPS</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">DRIPS is a novel CGRA architecture designed for dynamic rebalancing of data-dependent streaming applications.&lt;SEP&gt;DRIPS is a method or technique used to improve the throughput of graph convolutional networks by dynamically reconfiguring hardware resources based on execution status.&lt;SEP&gt;DRIPS stands for Dynamic Resource Inference and Pipeline Scheduling, a system designed to improve the throughput of graph neural network inference on CGRA.&lt;SEP&gt;DRIPS is a novel CGRA architecture that can dynamically rebalance data-dependent streaming applications.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-21d2d2feb71f0873f5e6a7016d1a0185&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-80f80a02f12f4e7d9000fea69ce18385&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1db998302836079483ae0d5d650ee931&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-072a87db7c5dbb5fd3ba6bae2d7254f2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-57a3a682d8c8b22c568166b68710bb5e</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1766410720</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
