  <data key="d0">depTable</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Records application's kernels dependencies and issues launch requests.&lt;SEP&gt;DepTable records application kernels dependencies and issues launch requests to the DRIPS Control Network.&lt;SEP&gt;depTable indicates dependencies between kernels and their configurations.&lt;SEP&gt;depTable is used by DRIPS Controller for preloading inter-kernel dependency.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-5dfdf451ecf45125ea01825c16c97036&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3c66229a13b9e7497d436c800b1c1873&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0411f37c55f5d083441c3ffdea010254&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0663013f37b4f7c3740127aa091def5f</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1766410728</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="DRIPS Controller">
  <data key="d0">DRIPS Controller</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">The DRIPS controller captures real-time execution status and enables dynamic rebalancing of the pipeline.&lt;SEP&gt;Manages kernel execution status and updates tile mappings.&lt;SEP&gt;The DRIPS Controller is responsible for triggering rebalancing, collecting execution information, and managing kernel dependencies.&lt;SEP&gt;The DRIPS Controller performs runtime operations such as fetching control signals and issuing requests.&lt;SEP&gt;DRIPS Controller is part of the DRIPS CGRA and manages control signals.&lt;SEP&gt;DRIPS Controller is responsible for preloading inter-kernel dependency in the application.&lt;SEP&gt;The DRIPS Controller determines that a kernel needs to be reconﬁgured and triggers the DMA unit.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-5dfdf451ecf45125ea01825c16c97036&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3c66229a13b9e7497d436c800b1c1873&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5de0c17cc29f5bae6ae53b83abd67cef&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-204207b9dedb6d8465abf466a8da7b22&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c70d15fac8cde95102112baf7572b83a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0411f37c55f5d083441c3ffdea010254&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0663013f37b4f7c3740127aa091def5f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2b8e7ceb7ade808ddedfa769ab7b31be&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-072a87db7c5dbb5fd3ba6bae2d7254f2</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1766410728</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="exeTable">
  <data key="d0">exeTable</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Collects the execution status of each kernel in exeTable.&lt;SEP&gt;ExeTable contains the execution cycles of kernels in the previous time window.&lt;SEP&gt;exeTable records the current execution status of pipelines.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-5dfdf451ecf45125ea01825c16c97036&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3c66229a13b9e7497d436c800b1c1873&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0411f37c55f5d083441c3ffdea010254</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1766410728</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
