<node id="GCN">
  <data key="d0">GCN</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">GCN stands for Graph Convolutional Network, a type of neural network used in graph-based machine learning.&lt;SEP&gt;GCN (Graph Convolutional Network) is evaluated with different sizes of time window on a 5×5 DRIPS CGRA.&lt;SEP&gt;Generalized Computation Node, one of the applications running on DRIPS.&lt;SEP&gt;GCN likely refers to a Graphics Core Next, a type of GPU or graphics processing unit.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-2b8e7ceb7ade808ddedfa769ab7b31be&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-072a87db7c5dbb5fd3ba6bae2d7254f2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c70d15fac8cde95102112baf7572b83a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0663013f37b4f7c3740127aa091def5f</data>
