<edge source="Coarse-Grained Reconfigurable Array (CGRA)" target="CGRAs">
  <data key="d7">1.0</data>
  <data key="d8">CGRAs are defined as Coarse-Grained Reconfigurable Arrays that offer a flexible yet energy-efficient alternative to general-purpose processors and accelerators.</data>
  <data key="d9">definition,hardware feature</data>
  <data key="d10">chunk-d3b54ca06794c60a35a49b96c496c299</data>
  <data key="d11">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d12">1766322497</data>
  <data key="d13"></data>
</edge>
<edge source="General Purpose Processors (CPU/GPU)" target="CGRAs">
  <data key="d7">1.0</data>
  <data key="d8">CGRAs outperform general-purpose processors in terms of perf/watt but offer lower flexibility than ASIC solutions.</data>
  <data key="d9">efficiency trade-off,performance comparison</data>
  <data key="d10">chunk-d3b54ca06794c60a35a49b96c496c299</data>
  <data key="d11">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d12">1766322498</data>
  <data key="d13"></data>
</edge>
<edge source="Application-Specific Integrated Circuit (ASIC)" target="CGRAs">
  <data key="d7">1.0</data>
  <data key="d8">While CGRAs offer better flexibility than ASICs, they may not outperform ASICs in terms of energy efficiency for specific tasks.</data>
  <data key="d9">efficiency trade-off,flexibility comparison</data>
  <data key="d10">chunk-d3b54ca06794c60a35a49b96c496c299</data>
  <data key="d11">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d12">1766322498</data>
  <data key="d13"></data>
</edge>
<edge source="Dataflow Graph (DFG)" target="CGRAs">
  <data key="d7">1.0</data>
  <data key="d8">CGRAs use DFG mapping for acceleration, which is a key technique in their design and functionality.</data>
  <data key="d9">acceleration mechanism,mapping approach</data>
  <data key="d10">chunk-d3b54ca06794c60a35a49b96c496c299</data>
  <data key="d11">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d12">1766322498</data>
  <data key="d13"></data>
</edge>
<edge source="Machine Learning Models" target="CGRAs">
  <data key="d7">1.0</data>
  <data key="d8">CGRAs are capable of supporting and accelerating a wide range of machine learning models through the ML-CGRA framework.</data>
  <data key="d9">hardware acceleration,model support</data>
  <data key="d10">chunk-d3b54ca06794c60a35a49b96c496c299</data>
  <data key="d11">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d12">1766322498</data>
  <data key="d13"></data>
</edge>
<edge source="Low-Level Instruction-Based Compiler Approaches" target="CGRAs">
  <data key="d7">1.0</data>
  <data key="d8">CGRAs currently use low-level instruction-based compilation approaches that lack the ability to fully leverage semantic information from ML models.</data>
  <data key="d9">compilation method,limitations</data>
  <data key="d10">chunk-d3b54ca06794c60a35a49b96c496c299</data>
  <data key="d11">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d12">1766322498</data>
  <data key="d13"></data>
</edge>
<edge source="Semantic Information" target="CGRAs">
  <data key="d7">1.0</data>
  <data key="d8">CGRAs can benefit significantly from the utilization of semantic information from ML models through the ML-CGRA framework.</data>
  <data key="d9">compilation improvement,model understanding</data>
  <data key="d10">chunk-d3b54ca06794c60a35a49b96c496c299</data>
  <data key="d11">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d12">1766322499</data>
  <data key="d13"></data>
</edge>
<edge source="Modern Deployments" target="CGRAs">
  <data key="d7">1.0</data>
  <data key="d8">CGRAs offer the flexibility needed for modern deployments while optimizing total power usage compared to general-purpose solutions.</data>
  <data key="d9">deployment flexibility,power usage optimization</data>
  <data key="d10">chunk-d3b54ca06794c60a35a49b96c496c299</data>
  <data key="d11">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d12">1766322499</data>
  <data key="d13"></data>
</edge>
<edge source="Performance Concerns" target="CGRA Runtime Library">
  <data key="d7">1.0</data>
  <data key="d8">The CGRA runtime library provides essential simulation tools for evaluating performance concerns and optimizing model implementations on CGRAs.</data>
