</edge>
<edge source="VecPAC" target="hybrid CGRA design">
  <data key="d7">1.0</data>
  <data key="d8">VecPAC is a hybrid design that maximizes performance across various application domains by combining scalar and vector functional units.</data>
  <data key="d9">application domains,performance maximization</data>
  <data key="d10">chunk-fb7fb6bd238c27a13ccbffd80022a059</data>
  <data key="d11">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d12">1766322538</data>
  <data key="d13"></data>
</edge>
<edge source="VecPAC" target="Fusion Capability">
  <data key="d7">1.0</data>
  <data key="d8">VecPAC's ability to fuse functional units is inspired by BitFusion, allowing it to minimize computation and communication on a per-layer basis.</data>
  <data key="d9">functional unit fusion,precision-awareness</data>
  <data key="d10">chunk-fb7fb6bd238c27a13ccbffd80022a059</data>
  <data key="d11">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d12">1766322539</data>
  <data key="d13"></data>
</edge>
<edge source="VecPAC" target="Coarse-Grained Reconfigurable Arrays">
  <data key="d7">1.0</data>
  <data key="d8">VecPAC is an innovative CGRA design that aims to balance specialization and adaptability.</data>
  <data key="d9">architecture innovation,design inspiration</data>
