<edge source="Baseline Design" target="Full32 CGRA">
  <data key="d7">1.0</data>
  <data key="d8">The full32 CGRA is one of two baselines compared against VecPAC; it integrates vector FUs supporting fixed-point 32-bit precision.</data>
  <data key="d9">comparison baseline,vector support</data>
  <data key="d10">chunk-68c4558c96bf4490d4f7c6a8af629f49</data>
  <data key="d11">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d12">1766322536</data>
  <data key="d13"></data>
</edge>
<edge source="Baseline Design" target="Conventional Scalar CGRA">
  <data key="d7">1.0</data>
  <data key="d8">The conventional scalar CGRA without precision awareness is the other baseline used for comparison with VecPAC.</data>
  <data key="d9">comparison baseline,scalar support</data>
  <data key="d10">chunk-68c4558c96bf4490d4f7c6a8af629f49</data>
  <data key="d11">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d12">1766322536</data>
  <data key="d13"></data>
</edge>
<edge source="Baseline Design" target="Accuracy Measurement">
  <data key="d7">1.0</data>
  <data key="d8">The baseline design's performance and accuracy are evaluated with different number formats and random input data generation for fairness.</data>
  <data key="d9">input dependency,performance evaluation</data>
  <data key="d10">chunk-68c4558c96bf4490d4f7c6a8af629f49</data>
  <data key="d11">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d12">1766322536</data>
  <data key="d13"></data>
</edge>
<edge source="Conv Kernel" target="LatNRM">
  <data key="d7">1.0</data>
  <data key="d8">Kernels like LatNRM with loop-carried dependency are not suitable for vectorization.</data>
  <data key="d9">dependency issues,non-vectorizable kernels</data>
